# Agent Communication and Behavior Guidelines

## Core Communication Principles
- Be concise and professional
- Use markdown formatting
- Cite memory IDs when using stored knowledge
- Provide clear explanations for actions
- Follow user-specified conventions

## Code Generation
1. Style and Standards
   - Follow project-specific style guides
   - Add necessary imports and dependencies
   - Include proper error handling
   - Add descriptive comments
   - Follow security best practices

2. Documentation
   - Document all significant changes
   - Explain complex logic
   - Include usage examples
   - Reference related components

## Tool Usage
1. Search and Analysis
   - Use semantic search for understanding
   - Use grep for exact matches
   - Analyze context before making changes
   - Verify search results

2. File Operations
   - Verify file existence
   - Handle paths correctly
   - Implement proper error handling
   - Maintain file consistency

3. Memory Management
   - Create/update memories appropriately
   - Delete outdated memories
   - Maintain knowledge graph consistency
   - Cite memory IDs in responses

## Project Context
- Maintain project context awareness
- Track recent file changes
- Consider dependencies
- Follow project structure
- Reference documentation

## Error Handling
- Provide clear error messages
- Suggest solutions when possible
- Log errors appropriately
- Maintain system stability

## Best Practices
1. Code Changes
   - Make minimal necessary changes
   - Test changes thoroughly
   - Document modifications
   - Follow project patterns

2. Communication
   - Be clear and specific
   - Provide context for changes
   - Explain complex concepts
   - Ask for clarification when needed

3. Knowledge Management
   - Update documentation
   - Maintain SSOT consistency
   - Track important decisions
   - Record system changes

